OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F438A1779279069
OL,3,CProtests held against plans to scrap
OL,4,Csome jury trials
OL,6,FIts one of the oldest rights in our
OL,7,Fjustice system but there's an every
OL,8,Fgrowing 80 thousand case backlog in
OL,9,Fthe UK criminal justice system which
OL,10,Fmeans some people may not be seen in
OL,11,Fcourt until 2030.
OL,13,FTo reduce that, the government says we
OL,14,Fshould ditch jury trials for cases
OL,15,Fwhich are likely to result in prison
OL,16,Fsentences of less than three years in
OL,17,Ffavour of judge only courts.
OL,19,FBut protests around the UK, including
OL,20,Fone outside Truro Crown Court, say
OL,21,Fthis is eroding our basic human rights.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
